<h2> Students Template </h2>
<p>
	<?=$html->image('gsoc2012_small.png');?>
	In order to apply successfully to Monkey Project, students must	send us the following template with the required answers.
</p>
<p>
<br>
Please send the following required information to the organization email <font class="email">gsoc2012@monkey-project.com</font>
</p>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<h1>About you</h1>
<br>

<li>Full name</li>
<li>E-Mail</li>
<li>Please provide us your primary phone number</li>

<li>Please provide any additional contact method as ICQ, Jabber, Gtalk, etc.</<li>

<li>We would like to have a backup contact, so please provide the name and contacts methods for a trusted
person that knows that you are participating on this program. This person should be able to know your
current status, maybe a friend or family member</li>

<li>Do you post on internet frequently ?, if so, please provide the address of your Blog, Twitter or
similar ?</li>

<li>How longer have you been using Linux as developer ?</li>

<li>Do you have any previous experience in FLOSS projects ?, if so please explain in detail. Please answer
of this question will NOT exclude you if you don't have previous experience</li>

<li>Describe your past experiences, credentials, prior projects, schoolwork, and that sort of information,
if possible, link to prior work or other resources as relevant.</li>

<br>
<h1>About your project</h1>
<br>

<li>What is the name of your project ?</li>

<li>Describe your project/proposal, provide full details.</li>

<li>What will be the benefit of Monkey project when the project is done ?</li>

<li>What is your timeline (tasks and dates associated) ?</li>

<br>
<h1>You and the community</h1>
<br>

<li>What will you do if you get stuck on your project and your mentor isn't around ?</li>

<li>How do you expect to keep the community informed about your progress ?</li>

<li>What are you plans when GSoC ends ?</li>


<br>
<h1>Miscellaneous</h1>
<br>
<li>Why Monkey Project ?</li>

<li>Are you interested into be a long term contributor of Monkey ?</li>

<li>Is this your first time participating in Summer of Code ?</li>

<li>Have you deal with HTTP servers performance before ?</li>

<li>What is your t-shirt size ?</li>

<li>Are you able to work full time on the project ?, if you have some extra activities please describe
them</li>

<li>Why should we choose you to complete the project in question ?</li>

<li>We have a "secret phrase" in our web site related to the GSoC, please find it (if you can) and drop us an
    email to gsoc2012@monkey-project.com :D</li>
</p>
<p>
<br>
Please consider to read the following link as an additional resource of help when writing an Application Proposals:<br><br>

